<div class="container mt-5">

  <!-- Page Title -->
  <h1 class="title has-text-centered has-text-primary">Marketing and E-Commerce Advice</h1>
  <p class="subtitle has-text-centered has-text-grey">Practical tips to help your startup succeed</p>

  <!-- Beginner Marketing Advice Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="title is-4 has-text-link">Marketing Tips for Beginners</h2>
    <div class="content">
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Know Your Target Audience:</strong> Research who your ideal customers are, their interests, and how they prefer to interact with businesses.</li>
        <li><strong>Build an Online Presence:</strong> Create profiles on social media platforms and ensure your business has a simple, professional website.</li>
        <li><strong>Start with Free Tools:</strong> Use tools like Google My Business for local exposure, Canva for graphic design, and Mailchimp for email campaigns.</li>
        <li><strong>Engage Consistently:</strong> Post regular updates, respond to customer inquiries, and interact with your audience through comments and messages.</li>
        <li><strong>Measure and Improve:</strong> Track your efforts using free tools like Google Analytics to see what works and adjust your strategies.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Social Media Focus Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="title is-4 has-text-link">Getting Started with Social Media</h2>
    <div class="content">
      <p>Social media is a powerful, low-cost way to market your business. Here are some beginner steps:</p>
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Choose One or Two Platforms:</strong> Start where your audience is. Facebook and Instagram are great for visuals, while LinkedIn is ideal for professionals.</li>
        <li><strong>Post Consistently:</strong> Set a schedule and stick to it—whether it's daily, weekly, or bi-weekly.</li>
        <li><strong>Use Engaging Content:</strong> Share updates, photos, behind-the-scenes looks, and success stories to connect with your audience.</li>
        <li><strong>Leverage Hashtags:</strong> Use relevant hashtags to increase the visibility of your posts.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- E-Commerce Advice Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="title is-4 has-text-link">E-Commerce Tips for Startups</h2>
    <div class="content">
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Optimize Your Website for Mobile:</strong> Ensure your e-commerce site is mobile-friendly, as most customers shop on their phones.</li>
        <li><strong>Offer Multiple Payment Options:</strong> Include credit/debit cards, digital wallets, and cash on delivery for accessibility.</li>
        <li><strong>Invest in Product Photography:</strong> High-quality images can make your products more appealing and increase trust.</li>
        <li><strong>Write Clear Product Descriptions:</strong> Highlight benefits, specifications, and unique selling points for each product.</li>
        <li><strong>Streamline the Checkout Process:</strong> Minimize the steps required to complete a purchase to reduce cart abandonment rates.</li>
        <li><strong>Leverage Customer Reviews:</strong> Encourage customers to leave reviews to build credibility and attract new buyers.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Marketing Strategies Section -->
  <section class="section">
    <h2 class="title is-4 has-text-link">Practical Marketing Strategies</h2>
    <div class="content">
      <ul class="list">
        <li><strong>Collaborate with Influencers:</strong> Partner with micro-influencers to promote your products to their niche audience.</li>
        <li><strong>Run Discounts and Promotions:</strong> Use limited-time offers to attract customers and drive sales.</li>
        <li><strong>Email Marketing:</strong> Build an email list and send newsletters with exclusive deals and updates.</li>
        <li><strong>Create Blog Content:</strong> Share informative and engaging content to attract organic traffic to your website.</li>
        <li><strong>Use Retargeting Ads:</strong> Show ads to customers who visited your site but didn’t make a purchase.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Free Tools for E-Commerce Section -->
  <section class="section">
